summary: eve went years without knowing villanelle existed; now that she does know, though, she can’t help but regret every moment...
body:
eve went years without knowing villanelle existed; now that she does know, though, she can’t help but regret every moment without her. she loves her posture, her pouting, her blasé dance through danger and disaster, 

she loves the way villanelle breathes in and out, like she knows life intimately

in a way, she does. more so than eve ever has, with eve’s safe flat and safe desk in MI5 and safe marriage bed, and dangerous secret hobbies that safely stay hobbies

villanelle doesn’t think about “safe”. villanelle is a fallen angel who clawed her way out of hell, breathing the fresh, lively air, clinging to the freedom not granted to her in her russian prison. her understanding of death, and, subsequently, of life, is like no other creature’s, and she absorbs every second of it without regret. she is not obligated to a rat race, not held down by holding back. she has grown to have a pure vitality and refuses to give an inch anymore to those that would hold her down, who would confine her to their way of breathing, who would suffocate her in the name of propriety and safety

eve would ruin those that try, just to watch those feline eyes flick towards her with approval, just to dip a finger into villanelle’s existence, to taste the divine flavor of life that envelops villanelle wherever she is

she would lose everything if it meant being able to dive into villanelle’s world,

and she just might drown in it
